WEBVTT

00:17.784 --> 00:19.718
(bellowing)

00:19.720 --> 00:21.387
Yee-haw-ho-ho!

00:22.522 --> 00:24.757
(school bell ringing)

00:27.127 --> 00:29.194
(bears growling)

00:29.996 --> 00:32.197
(whistle blows)

00:43.676 --> 00:47.713
(playing "Jingle Bells")

00:48.481 --> 00:50.716
(playing bluesy riff)

00:56.990 --> 00:59.224
♪

01:09.903 --> 01:11.770
(growls)

01:13.006 --> 01:15.507
(snarling)

01:15.509 --> 01:17.576
(squawking)

01:17.578 --> 01:20.345
(cats yowling)
(Cat Lady jabbering)

01:23.516 --> 01:25.017
D'oh!

01:25.019 --> 01:26.585
(bicycle bell jingling)

01:26.587 --> 01:28.921
(grunts)

01:36.262 --> 01:38.464
BART: <i>Ay, caramba!</i>

01:41.868 --> 01:44.103
(groans)
Carrot.

02:01.788 --> 02:03.989
(humming)

02:06.092 --> 02:08.760
You are about to see
the worst half-hour

02:08.762 --> 02:10.629
of television ever.

02:10.631 --> 02:12.397
All righty then.

02:13.399 --> 02:15.834
♪

02:15.836 --> 02:17.803
Okay, R3, let's
serve up some soup.

02:17.805 --> 02:20.939
(whistling)

02:20.941 --> 02:23.942
May the <i>sauce</i> be with you.

02:23.944 --> 02:25.611
Oh, since when is soup sauce?

02:25.613 --> 02:27.646
This is so non-canonical.

02:27.648 --> 02:30.549
You have every right
to be furious.

02:34.954 --> 02:36.421
Oh, it's as bad
as I remembered,

02:36.423 --> 02:38.790
and I haven't watched
it since yesterday.

02:38.792 --> 02:41.827
<i>Horrible, yet enthralling.</i>

02:41.829 --> 02:43.328
Hooray!

02:43.330 --> 02:45.864
A card from Dr. Hibbert.

02:45.866 --> 02:48.033
(gasps)

02:49.802 --> 02:51.770
Phew.

02:51.772 --> 02:54.173
Oh.

02:54.175 --> 02:55.641
(bird squawks)

02:55.643 --> 02:57.176
I'll be right home, honey.

02:57.178 --> 03:00.345
I just got to lock down
the reactor for the evening.

03:05.051 --> 03:07.019
Tight as a drum.

03:08.121 --> 03:09.821
See you soon.

03:09.823 --> 03:12.191
Bart, hold the ladder still!

03:12.193 --> 03:13.692
(gasps)

03:14.694 --> 03:16.628
(grunts)

03:17.697 --> 03:18.964
Oh!

03:18.966 --> 03:20.699
Wish Homer was here.

03:21.568 --> 03:22.668
Simpson!

03:22.670 --> 03:23.902
(gasps)
Mr. Scrooge!

03:23.904 --> 03:26.572
Time for your holiday gift.
Ooh!

03:26.574 --> 03:29.341
In your name, a donation has
been made...
(groans)

03:29.343 --> 03:30.976
...to the Salvation Army.

03:30.978 --> 03:32.744
(groans)
Also, you will be visited

03:32.746 --> 03:34.713
by three spirits tonight.

03:34.715 --> 03:36.415
No, wait. That's my schedule.

03:36.417 --> 03:38.717
Smithers, We need to cancel
the 10:30 spirit.

03:38.719 --> 03:39.918
Yes, sir.

03:39.920 --> 03:41.553
(Marge humming)

03:42.355 --> 03:44.389
MARGE: Hello.

03:44.391 --> 03:45.524
HOMER:
Heading home, baby.

03:45.526 --> 03:46.858
Nothing's gonna stop me now.

03:46.860 --> 03:48.393
(shrieks)

03:51.431 --> 03:53.365
(groaning)
Maybe a drink

03:53.367 --> 03:55.934
will help me with my driving.

04:00.740 --> 04:03.408
Man, those things go off quick.

04:04.043 --> 04:05.377
♪ Yo.

04:05.379 --> 04:06.445
(guitar plays country melody)

04:06.447 --> 04:08.013
(metal guitar plays)
♪ Ah!

04:08.015 --> 04:09.748
VIN SCULLY:
...and the baseball exclaimed

04:09.750 --> 04:11.850
as it flew out of sight,

04:11.852 --> 04:15.387
this ballpark is shorter
in left field than right.

04:15.389 --> 04:17.022
Martinez swings and misses.

04:17.024 --> 04:20.058
Yes! I'm recording this
during a game.

04:20.060 --> 04:21.360
Since the United States
government

04:21.362 --> 04:23.862
declares this man
to be Santa Claus,

04:23.864 --> 04:25.731
this court will not dispute it.

04:25.733 --> 04:27.599
Few people know that verdict

04:27.601 --> 04:30.302
was overturned in the sequel.
(chuckles)

04:30.304 --> 04:33.038
I better be heading
home to my family.

04:33.040 --> 04:36.141
Enjoy your evening
with your wonderful...

04:36.143 --> 04:38.744
uh... neon sign.

04:38.746 --> 04:41.913
Yeah, last year I broke it just
so the repairman would come.

04:41.915 --> 04:44.216
But I'll be fine.

04:45.718 --> 04:47.452
Hey, um, you gonna be okay?

04:47.454 --> 04:48.954
Oh, yeah, yeah.

04:48.956 --> 04:51.123
Super! (crying)

04:54.761 --> 04:55.794
It's just that...

04:55.796 --> 04:56.995
you know, I lost my ma

04:56.997 --> 04:58.964
at Christmas.
(sighs)

04:58.966 --> 05:01.466
She took me to a mall,
and I never saw her again.

05:01.468 --> 05:02.634
But I'll never forget that image

05:02.636 --> 05:04.503
of her bolting
for the parking lot.

05:04.505 --> 05:06.505
Okay, okay.
I'll stay for one beer.

05:06.507 --> 05:08.974
Oh, great, great.
But don't do it out of pity.

05:08.976 --> 05:11.476
Pity! Pity! Have pity!

05:11.478 --> 05:13.812
Look, I'm wrapped
around your leg here!

05:13.814 --> 05:15.447
Please! Please! Please!

05:15.449 --> 05:17.249
But I promised Marge.

05:17.251 --> 05:19.785
Now I'm sitting on
your shoulders! Please!

05:19.787 --> 05:21.286
Okay, okay!

05:21.288 --> 05:23.088
(Homer groans)

05:24.691 --> 05:26.525
(grunts)

05:26.527 --> 05:27.926
Mom, where's Dad?

05:27.928 --> 05:29.995
I don't know.

05:29.997 --> 05:31.463
Aw, it's Christmas Eve, man!

05:31.465 --> 05:32.931
We do not want
to set a precedent

05:32.933 --> 05:35.133
for fat guys
being late tonight!

05:35.135 --> 05:37.035
(grunts)

05:37.037 --> 05:40.005
♪ Silent night

05:40.007 --> 05:43.208
♪ Holy night...

05:43.210 --> 05:45.644
(laughs)
I'm happy on Christmas Eve.

05:45.646 --> 05:48.046
And for once it's not
'cause some drunk

05:48.048 --> 05:49.815
left a wallet on his stool.

05:49.817 --> 05:52.751
<i>Uh-oh, this is</i>
<i>starting to hurt.</i>

05:55.788 --> 05:58.023
(grunts)

05:58.025 --> 06:01.860
And now, Homer, it's only fair
that I give yous a gift.

06:01.862 --> 06:05.630
I'm gonna set the clock
in the bar to the correct time.

06:05.632 --> 06:07.733
HOMER:
Hey, what the...

06:07.735 --> 06:10.068
(gasps)
I am so late!

06:11.537 --> 06:13.739
Whoa, whoa.
It's the night before Christmas!

06:13.741 --> 06:15.540
Stop stirring, you!

06:15.542 --> 06:16.675
(grunts)

06:16.677 --> 06:18.910
(ticking)

06:20.246 --> 06:21.913
One night.

06:21.915 --> 06:23.415
The one night of the year

06:23.417 --> 06:25.050
I want Homer home
with his family,

06:25.052 --> 06:26.985
and he can't even do that.

06:26.987 --> 06:30.055
Christmas is a great time
to dump him.

06:30.057 --> 06:32.758
If you do it now, you won't have
to watch the Super Bowl.

06:32.760 --> 06:35.093
(tires squealing,
car door closing)

06:38.664 --> 06:40.866
Homer Simpson!

06:40.868 --> 06:42.768
(gasps)
I never thought I'd say this

06:42.770 --> 06:44.069
to someone I cared for,

06:44.071 --> 06:46.071
much less my husband,

06:46.073 --> 06:47.672
but I'm saying it now.

06:47.674 --> 06:50.275
I don't want you here
on Christmas!

06:50.277 --> 06:52.244
Marge, think about
what you're saying.

06:52.246 --> 06:54.780
It's Sir Isaac Newton's
birthday.

06:54.782 --> 06:57.082
Out now!

06:59.252 --> 07:00.685
Yeah? Well, good luck

07:00.687 --> 07:02.954
assembling all those
toys without me!

07:02.956 --> 07:04.423
We already did it.

07:04.425 --> 07:07.259
(shrieks)
The ghost of Marge Future!

07:13.733 --> 07:14.966
HOMER:
<i>She'll forgive me.</i>

07:14.968 --> 07:16.735
MARGE:
<i>Should I forgive him?</i>

07:16.737 --> 07:18.136
HOMER:
<i>Especially this time.</i>

07:18.138 --> 07:20.172
MARGE:
<i>Maybe not this time.</i>

07:21.375 --> 07:24.209
MARGE:
<i>With his marriage</i>
<i>in this much trouble,</i>

07:24.211 --> 07:26.545
<i>he's got a lot</i>
<i>of thinking to do.</i>

07:26.547 --> 07:29.981
HOMER:
<i>I wonder if there's birds</i>
<i>on the moon.</i>

07:29.983 --> 07:33.452
(sobbing):
I miss Marge.

07:35.321 --> 07:38.924
<i>I wonder if Lou suspects</i>
<i>that I was his Secret Santa.</i>

07:38.926 --> 07:40.559
<i>What kind of a cheapskate</i>
<i>gives you</i>

07:40.561 --> 07:42.727
<i>one corncob holder</i>
<i>for Christmas?</i>

07:42.729 --> 07:44.162
(chuckles)

07:47.133 --> 07:50.602
Moe, what are you doing?

07:50.604 --> 07:53.438
♪ Good King Wenceslas
looked out ♪

07:53.440 --> 07:55.240
♪ On the feast...

07:55.242 --> 07:57.342
JAPANESE MALE VOICE:
Voice too poor for karaoke.

07:57.344 --> 07:59.911
Shutting down.

07:59.913 --> 08:02.113
Bye now.
Oh, my God.

08:02.115 --> 08:04.616
Santa brought me
just what I asked for!

08:04.618 --> 08:06.318
(laughs)

08:06.320 --> 08:08.487
Hmm. "239."

08:08.489 --> 08:10.388
Who's he fooling?

08:11.424 --> 08:12.924
Hmm... Hmm.

08:12.926 --> 08:14.125
Hmm!

08:14.127 --> 08:15.460
Mm-hmm.

08:15.462 --> 08:19.264
Hey, pal. Can't believe you have
to work Christmas Eve.

08:19.266 --> 08:21.366
Well, if you're here
for a last minute gift,

08:21.368 --> 08:23.335
we have a cell phone
holder that fits

08:23.337 --> 08:25.937
no cell phone
made after 2002.

08:25.939 --> 08:27.939
And, uh, Kwik-E-Nog.

08:27.941 --> 08:29.207
Nog stands for

08:29.209 --> 08:31.510
"Not Okayed by Government."

08:31.512 --> 08:34.179
Maybe Marge would forgive me

08:34.181 --> 08:35.680
if I won the lotto.

08:35.682 --> 08:36.815
Give me a scratcher.

08:36.817 --> 08:38.216
D'oh!
Give me another one.

08:38.218 --> 08:39.618
(groans)
D'oh!

08:39.620 --> 08:40.619
Give me another one.

08:40.621 --> 08:41.686
(groans)
D'oh!

08:41.688 --> 08:42.954
Give me another one.
(groans)

08:42.956 --> 08:44.155
D'oh!
Give me another one.

08:44.157 --> 08:45.357
(groans)
D'oh!

08:45.359 --> 08:46.391
Give me another one.

08:46.393 --> 08:47.826
Oh please, stop! Stop it!

08:47.828 --> 08:49.661
My religion prohibits me
from taking advantage

08:49.663 --> 08:51.563
of a fool more
than ten times.

08:51.565 --> 08:54.032
This thing basically
has no winners.

08:54.034 --> 08:56.067
Yeah, but doesn't
the money goes to schools?

08:56.069 --> 08:58.837
You have been to our schools.
What do you think?

08:58.839 --> 09:02.307
Welcome to Bring Us
Your Toilet Paper night.

09:02.309 --> 09:04.643
Don't worry,
none goes to Willie.

09:04.645 --> 09:06.044
Don't need it.

09:06.046 --> 09:07.879
I got me Starbucks napkins!

09:07.881 --> 09:10.482
You know, ironically, in
India, they did use the money

09:10.484 --> 09:13.251
for schools and they
had fantastic results.

09:13.253 --> 09:15.554
Aw, thanks
for your honesty, Apu.

09:15.556 --> 09:16.988
Is there any other product
in the store

09:16.990 --> 09:18.223
you'd like to warn me about?

09:18.225 --> 09:19.558
Well, uh...

09:19.560 --> 09:23.161
those hot dogs began
life as Twinkies.

09:25.665 --> 09:27.365
(sizzling)

09:27.367 --> 09:28.533
Wow.

09:28.535 --> 09:31.002
(pop, crackling)

09:31.004 --> 09:33.104
(groans)
Christmas Eve.

09:33.106 --> 09:34.706
The one night a kid
wants to go to sleep

09:34.708 --> 09:36.274
is the one night he can't.

09:36.276 --> 09:37.776
I can't have another cocoa.

09:37.778 --> 09:39.911
My pee is starting to
smell like a ski chalet.

09:39.913 --> 09:42.213
(door opens)
Oh, thank God you're here.

09:42.215 --> 09:43.381
I need to get to sleep.

09:43.383 --> 09:44.883
Tell me the story
of jazz again.

09:44.885 --> 09:47.519
Well, the story of jazz starts
with the tresillo,

09:47.521 --> 09:49.888
the most prevalent
duple-pulse rhythmic cell

09:49.890 --> 09:51.423
in sub-Saharan African music.

09:51.425 --> 09:52.457
But the rest will have to wait.

09:52.459 --> 09:54.426
Bart, Bart,
I hear Mom sobbing.

09:54.428 --> 09:56.227
And I don't know where Dad is.

09:56.229 --> 09:58.897
If it helps, I made you a card.

09:58.899 --> 10:01.299
Bart, this is the year
I've got to nail Christmas.

10:01.301 --> 10:03.969
I don't want to be a jaded
ten-year-old like you!

10:03.971 --> 10:05.270
Ah, yes.

10:05.272 --> 10:07.939
I remember Christmas Eve
when I was eight.

10:07.941 --> 10:10.408
MARGE:
Why do you always wait
till the last minute

10:10.410 --> 10:11.910
to put up the lights?

10:11.912 --> 10:13.445
HOMER:
I don't want to ruin the magic.

10:13.447 --> 10:15.213
And I certainly... Aah!

10:15.215 --> 10:16.915
(gurgling)

10:16.917 --> 10:18.483
Next year

10:18.485 --> 10:19.551
this is

10:19.553 --> 10:20.885
your job.

10:20.887 --> 10:23.421
(electrical crackling)
(grunting)

10:23.423 --> 10:25.323
(grunting)

10:25.325 --> 10:26.925
Ooh!

10:26.927 --> 10:28.393
(grunting)

10:28.395 --> 10:31.463
Hmm, they say a boy never
gets over seeing his dad

10:31.465 --> 10:32.664
in a Santa suit getting hanged

10:32.666 --> 10:34.265
and electrocuted
on Christmas Eve.

10:34.267 --> 10:35.867
I'll help you, kid.

10:39.972 --> 10:42.173
(sighs heavily)

10:53.986 --> 10:55.654
Mom, I'm just a kid,

10:55.656 --> 10:58.523
but I say if Dad isn't
here Christmas morning,

10:58.525 --> 11:00.959
that's the kind of thing
families never recover from.

11:00.961 --> 11:02.527
Hmm.

11:02.529 --> 11:06.097
Lisa, sweetie,
I'm tired of being a pushover.

11:06.099 --> 11:07.298
You're not a pushover.

11:07.300 --> 11:08.466
You can't smoke.

11:08.468 --> 11:09.701
Just chewing
on the wood.

11:09.703 --> 11:10.935
Okay then.

11:10.937 --> 11:12.470
(clattering)

11:12.472 --> 11:14.005
(groans)

11:14.007 --> 11:15.440
Eh, how you doing there?

11:15.442 --> 11:17.308
Uh, your front
door was locked,

11:17.310 --> 11:19.477
So, uh, rather than
call or knock,

11:19.479 --> 11:21.513
I, uh, came down
your chimbley there.

11:21.515 --> 11:23.181
(coughs)

11:24.116 --> 11:27.152
Moe Szyslak, you didn't
climb down our chimney

11:27.154 --> 11:28.953
just to say
"Merry Christmas."

11:28.955 --> 11:30.155
(coughing)

11:30.157 --> 11:31.456
(clears throat)

11:31.458 --> 11:33.191
Midge, it's one minute
till Christmas,

11:33.193 --> 11:35.794
and if I'm ever gonna be
a good guy, it's now.

11:35.796 --> 11:37.028
All right, here I go.

11:37.030 --> 11:39.197
I'm the one that kept Homer
from coming home,

11:39.199 --> 11:41.466
'cause, uh, well, I was lonely.

11:41.468 --> 11:43.301
(gasps)
Yeah, that's right--

11:43.303 --> 11:44.536
me, Mr. Party Pants.

11:44.538 --> 11:47.739
So, uh, so don't hold
it against Homer, eh?

11:47.741 --> 11:50.542
Oh, my poor Homie.

11:50.544 --> 11:52.410
This is what
I was hoping for.

11:52.412 --> 11:56.147
For it <i>not</i> to have been
<i>completely</i> his fault.

11:56.149 --> 11:57.682
Thank you, Moe.

11:57.684 --> 11:58.817
(mumbling):
Huh?

11:58.819 --> 12:00.485
I'm sorry, Marge,
I'm sorry,

12:00.487 --> 12:02.921
but it was Christmas, and
we were under the mistletoe.

12:02.923 --> 12:04.556
That's lettuce caught
in a spider's web.

12:04.558 --> 12:05.757
All right.

12:05.759 --> 12:07.492
I've got
to call Homer.

12:08.327 --> 12:09.527
(buzzing)

12:09.529 --> 12:11.062
(beeps)

12:13.866 --> 12:15.633
D'oh!

12:17.436 --> 12:19.404
What gives? Don't you get
Showtime Extreme?

12:19.406 --> 12:21.406
(groans)
No answer.

12:21.408 --> 12:23.441
Let's go find
your father.

12:23.443 --> 12:25.176
What?

12:25.178 --> 12:27.178
I never give up hope.

12:27.180 --> 12:28.613
Neither do I.

12:32.284 --> 12:34.819
Even the anchor store's closed.

12:36.122 --> 12:39.124
("Someday at Christmas" plays)

12:40.426 --> 12:43.061
♪ Someday at Christmas

12:43.063 --> 12:45.563
♪ Men won't be boys

12:45.565 --> 12:47.599
♪ Playing with bombs

12:47.601 --> 12:50.468
♪ Like kids play with toys

12:50.470 --> 12:54.939
♪ One warm December
our hearts will see ♪

12:54.941 --> 12:59.544
♪ A world where men are free

12:59.546 --> 13:01.479
♪ Mm

13:01.481 --> 13:03.114
♪ Someday at Christmas...

13:03.116 --> 13:04.983
Any uplifting
holiday movies?

13:04.985 --> 13:06.651
Well, let's see.

13:06.653 --> 13:09.220
We've got a film about
a nutty professor...
Ooh.

13:09.222 --> 13:10.755
...with advanced
Alzheimer's.

13:10.757 --> 13:11.956
D'oh!

13:11.958 --> 13:13.558
Seth Rogen and
Jonah Hill...
Yeah?

13:13.560 --> 13:15.727
...in a concentration
camp drama.

13:15.729 --> 13:16.728
D'oh!

13:16.730 --> 13:18.163
And a cute model...
Ooh!

13:18.165 --> 13:20.598
...airplane that
lost its propeller.

13:20.600 --> 13:24.402
Um, I guess I'll take
the concentration camp one.

13:24.404 --> 13:27.071
And a Merry Christmas
to you, sir.

13:27.073 --> 13:29.908
♪

13:29.910 --> 13:31.242
(sighs)

13:31.244 --> 13:33.478
Well, if I got to spend
Christmas Eve alone,

13:33.480 --> 13:35.280
at least no one will see me.

13:35.282 --> 13:37.682
Hey-ya, Homer!
(barking)

13:37.684 --> 13:39.918
Ah, just 'cause you're here
shouldn't make you sad.

13:39.920 --> 13:43.154
This is my 17th Christmas
alone in a movie theater.

13:43.156 --> 13:44.689
This is my family.

13:44.691 --> 13:46.524
The guy with
the smelly pants,

13:46.526 --> 13:49.928
the lady that carries
empty cans in a PBS tote bag.

13:49.930 --> 13:52.931
Ugh, what if I left now and gave
you guys my popcorn and soda?

13:52.933 --> 13:54.399
(cat meows)

13:55.201 --> 13:57.836
Wow, Homer, you have
a very generous side.

13:57.838 --> 14:01.339
Can I borrow,
like, $10,000?

14:05.177 --> 14:07.345
Flanders?
What are you doing here?

14:07.347 --> 14:08.980
Christmas is
my busy season.

14:08.982 --> 14:11.015
Sold three pairs of
scissors this month.

14:11.017 --> 14:12.517
Two came back.

14:12.519 --> 14:14.319
Say, Flanders,

14:14.321 --> 14:18.223
with all the hard luck you've
had, how do you stay so happy?

14:18.225 --> 14:20.291
And don't say
"Jesus."

14:20.293 --> 14:23.862
Well, sir, our good Lord and
my boys are all I've really got.

14:23.864 --> 14:25.897
All Edna left me was
wonderful memories

14:25.899 --> 14:27.832
and some
ungraded papers,

14:27.834 --> 14:29.901
which I'm still working
my way through. (sniffles)

14:29.903 --> 14:31.836
Flanders,
are you crying?

14:31.838 --> 14:34.539
Ah, just snowflakes
on my mustache.

14:34.541 --> 14:37.342
Listen, could I buy
a left-handed, uh...

14:37.344 --> 14:39.043
I don't know,
eyelash curler?

14:39.045 --> 14:41.713
Sure, but y-your eyelashes are
long and luxurious already.

14:41.715 --> 14:43.748
Are you just buying this
to be nice?

14:43.750 --> 14:47.085
Uh, maybe.

14:47.087 --> 14:50.054
Oh, Homer, unto us this
day, a neighbor is born.

14:50.056 --> 14:51.589
But why?

14:51.591 --> 14:55.660
Because jerk-ass Homer
has become ass-jerk Homer.

14:55.662 --> 14:58.730
Well, that curled my
lashes, but good for you.

14:58.732 --> 14:59.898
(chuckles)

14:59.900 --> 15:02.166
You're all right,
stupid Flanders.

15:02.168 --> 15:03.368
You're all right.

15:03.370 --> 15:06.371
Well, this is a whole new
relationship for us.

15:06.373 --> 15:08.673
We'll be friends
in this life and the next.

15:08.675 --> 15:10.675
HOMER:
<i>Whoa, he's getting serious.</i>

15:10.677 --> 15:12.110
<i>Is this what I really want?</i>

15:12.112 --> 15:13.278
(whimpering)

15:13.280 --> 15:16.281
My best friend is
a great runner.

15:21.086 --> 15:24.122
I made everyone happy but me.

15:24.124 --> 15:26.057
Some Christmas.

15:26.059 --> 15:28.259
(sobbing):
<i>Feliz navidad.</i>

15:32.431 --> 15:34.632
(wind whistling)

15:39.939 --> 15:42.273
(vehicle approaching,
tires screeching)

15:44.143 --> 15:46.044
Abe Simpson, please.

15:46.046 --> 15:48.112
Visitor for
Abe Simpson.

15:48.114 --> 15:49.314
You came!

15:49.316 --> 15:50.782
You came to see me!

15:50.784 --> 15:52.283
(Bart grunting)
Aw!

15:52.285 --> 15:54.786
Easter came early
this year.

15:54.788 --> 15:56.754
I thought we were just
gonna ask if he'd seen Homer.

15:56.756 --> 15:59.324
I'm afraid we've
awoken a needy giant.

15:59.326 --> 16:01.159
Visitors!

16:01.161 --> 16:03.928
Let's brew some weak tea and
talk about the good ol' days!

16:03.930 --> 16:06.798
Make them turn
the TV to CBS!

16:07.967 --> 16:11.302
("Hark! The Herald
Angels Sing" plays)

16:12.237 --> 16:14.472
(electrical crackling)

16:15.341 --> 16:18.676
Well, with all that you
folks have experienced,

16:18.678 --> 16:22.146
I think we could enjoy listening
to a little of your wisdom.

16:22.148 --> 16:24.649
The problem with
Puerto Ricans is...

16:24.651 --> 16:26.484
No casual racism.

16:26.486 --> 16:28.186
(snoring)

16:28.188 --> 16:30.321
(muttering)

16:31.357 --> 16:33.558
What the...?

16:35.461 --> 16:37.028
The Nutcracker.

16:37.030 --> 16:39.998
Every child's favorite
Christmas character.

16:40.000 --> 16:41.432
Is this a dream?

16:41.434 --> 16:42.800
Not a dream.

16:42.802 --> 16:44.102
I work at the mall.

16:44.104 --> 16:46.104
And it's closed, so scram.

16:46.106 --> 16:47.772
Man, you are a nutcracker.

16:47.774 --> 16:49.340
But I've learned
something tonight--

16:49.342 --> 16:50.708
you know how everyone hates

16:50.710 --> 16:52.777
being with their family
on Christmas?
Uh-huh.

16:52.779 --> 16:54.712
Well, being without them
is worse.

16:54.714 --> 16:57.982
Can you find it in your wooden
heart to give me a break?

16:57.984 --> 17:00.184
All right, listen,
pal, uh...

17:00.186 --> 17:02.286
you want to go
to a party?

17:02.288 --> 17:04.522
(dance music plays)

17:17.536 --> 17:19.203
What are you
doing here?

17:19.205 --> 17:23.007
Halloween merchandise goes
on sale December 26, man.

17:23.009 --> 17:25.243
("O Holy Night" plays)

17:31.750 --> 17:34.585
Well, he's not in
the neon sign store.

17:34.587 --> 17:36.254
Lady, buy a sign
or go home.

17:36.256 --> 17:38.022
I'm sorry.

17:38.024 --> 17:40.858
I'm trying to find my husband,
and nothing's open.

17:40.860 --> 17:42.860
Well, there is
a party here.

17:42.862 --> 17:45.196
Hey, is your husband into
people dressed like food?

17:45.198 --> 17:47.165
Where is this party?!

17:47.167 --> 17:48.866
(electrical crackling)

17:48.868 --> 17:51.069
♪

17:51.071 --> 17:53.104
Oh, my God.

17:53.106 --> 17:55.306
Is that girl really doing that?!

18:02.748 --> 18:05.183
Mm, load-bearing wall.

18:07.619 --> 18:09.821
(whoops)

18:11.223 --> 18:14.092
(moans)

18:14.094 --> 18:16.360
Ho, ho, ho!

18:16.362 --> 18:17.695
<i>This party's great,</i>

18:17.697 --> 18:19.964
<i>but all I wish is</i>
<i>that I was drinking a beer</i>

18:19.966 --> 18:21.799
<i>with my kids right now.</i>

18:21.801 --> 18:23.401
MARGE:
Homer?
Hmm?!

18:23.403 --> 18:26.370
Homie, I'm
your present tonight.

18:26.372 --> 18:29.407
And the present is that
I'm not gonna always assume

18:29.409 --> 18:30.975
that you screwed up.

18:30.977 --> 18:33.478
Because I realize maybe
there's a good explanation

18:33.480 --> 18:34.912
for what you do.

18:34.914 --> 18:37.115
Or a crazy one that's
pretty entertaining.

18:37.117 --> 18:40.251
Oh, Marge,
you found me!

18:40.253 --> 18:42.053
You always find me.

18:42.055 --> 18:44.822
Now we just have to find your
car in the mall parking lot.

18:44.824 --> 18:47.492
I thought I had one of
those chirping keys.

18:47.494 --> 18:50.094
Oh, well, I've been
faking the noise.

18:50.096 --> 18:51.762
'Cause you deserve
the best.

18:51.764 --> 18:52.830
(imitates car chirp)

18:52.832 --> 18:54.432
You didn't have
to do that.

18:54.434 --> 18:56.334
I love you
just the same.

18:56.336 --> 18:57.502
(imitates car chirp)

18:57.504 --> 18:59.871
(moaning)

19:01.607 --> 19:04.242
Thank you magical creatures
of the mall!

19:04.244 --> 19:06.744
You have all taught me
a Christmas message

19:06.746 --> 19:08.312
I'll never forget--

19:08.314 --> 19:12.083
the place to get drunk
is at home.

19:21.693 --> 19:23.594
("Dance of the Sugar Plum Fairy"
plays)

19:33.338 --> 19:35.106
All right, I'm
sick of waiting.

19:35.108 --> 19:37.141
Bart, you know you
can't open a present

19:37.143 --> 19:38.509
till Mom and
Dad wake up.

19:38.511 --> 19:40.511
(scoffs)
It's 9:10 a.m.

19:40.513 --> 19:43.281
I know what they're doing--
they're up in bed

19:43.283 --> 19:46.017
watching the re-broadcast of
the Hollywood Christmas Parade.

19:46.019 --> 19:47.685
Oops, my finger slipped.

19:47.687 --> 19:49.620
Oops! So did mine.

19:49.622 --> 19:51.522
(laughing)
Oh, I got a baseball glove.

19:51.524 --> 19:52.957
I got a chemistry set.

19:52.959 --> 19:54.725
I want yours.

19:58.697 --> 20:00.631
Merry Christmas,
son.

20:00.633 --> 20:02.733
Uh, don't you mean
"Happy Birthday"?

20:02.735 --> 20:05.069
It's two presents.

20:05.071 --> 20:07.138
Um, walkie-talkies don't
count as two presents.

20:07.140 --> 20:08.539
God.

20:08.541 --> 20:10.741
I mean, you.

20:15.214 --> 20:17.081
JESUS:
<i>Idiot.</i>

20:17.083 --> 20:20.384
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH
access.wgbh.org

20:22.521 --> 20:25.022
Behold, our
miracle of birth.

20:25.024 --> 20:27.892
Each birth is followed
by another birth

20:27.894 --> 20:29.260
just seconds later.

20:29.262 --> 20:30.895
(grunting)

20:35.867 --> 20:38.002
What the?!
This isn't Halloween.

21:17.909 --> 21:20.144
Shh!
